    <div id="header-content">
      <hgroup id="header-group">
        <h1>My Path, My Web Thimble Build</h1>
        <h2>Use Thimble to imagine your own path into computing and webmaking with your inspiration, makes, and hopes for the future.</h2>
      </hgroup>
      <div id="metadata">
        <span id="made-by">Made by MozFest 2013 Girls in Technology Scrum Group</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div id="content">
    <div id="left-side">

      <section class="step-section">
        <h1 class="big-green-title">Steps for the Activity</h1>
        <ol>

          <li>
            <p>Explain the structure of the <a href="https://chadsansing.makes.org/thimble/my-path-my-web" target="_blank">My Path, My Web Thimble template</a> so that participants know how to swap out the default images for their own, and so that participants know the entire page is hackable through Thimble remix.</p>
          </li>

          <li>
          <p>Help participants explore the template's code to locate the divs that hold the images.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Help participants upload and share photos or videos for each of the three stages in their path ("My Inspiration", "My Make" and "My Future") to use in their own Thimble remixes. If your group completed the Popcorn or <a href="https://stephguthrie.makes.org/thimble/hacking-my-media-with-xray-goggles" target="_blank">X-Ray Goggles</a> activities in this teaching kit, embeds or screenshots of their finished makes from these activities would be perfect for the "My Make" stage. If needed, help them search open photo repositories for images to use and credit in their My Path, My Web makes.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
          <p>Work with participants to troubleshoot any sizing, layout, or other coding issues that come up in their remixes.</p>
           <li>
             <p>Share a group <a href="https://login.persona.org/" target="_blank">Persona</a> login or help participants create their own logins (with parent permission and accounts when necessary) to publish, share and discuss their remixes as a group.</p>
          </li>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div id="right-side">

  

      <section class="small-checkbox-section">
        <h1><i class="icon-check-sign"></i> Materials</h1>
